        "title": "7. PRIMARY SOURCES",
        "body": "| # | Source | Title | Author/Publisher | Date | Type | Reliability |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | WWA | Rapid attribution analysis: June 2026 European heatwave | World Weather Attribution / Theodore Keeping, Imperial College London | Jun 26 | Independent Verification | Very High |\n| 2 | WHO | Press conference on European heatwave deaths | WHO Director-General Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus | Jun 28 | Official Statement | Very High |\n| 3 | Public Health France | Excess mortality data, June 21-29 | Santé Publique France | Jun 28-29 | Official Statement | High |\n| 4 | Météo-France | National thermal indicator data | Météo-France | Jun 22-26 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 5 | UK Met Office | Red heat warning data / June records | UK Met Office | Jun 23-25 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 6 | DWD | German temperature records — 252 stations | Deutscher Wetterdienst | Jun 28 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 7 | CHMI | Czech all-time temperature record | Czech Hydrometeorological Institute | Jun 28 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 8 | IMGW | Polish all-time temperature record (105-year record broken) | Polish Institute of Meteorology | Jun 28 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 9 | Hungarian Met Service | Hungarian all-time record 42.0°C | Hungarian Meteorological Service | Jun 29 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 10 | Slovak Hydromet Institute | Slovak all-time record 41.0°C | Slovak Hydrometeorological Institute | Jun 29 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 11 | Danish Met Institute | Danish all-time record 37.0°C (since 1874) | Danish Meteorological Institute | Jun 27 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 12 | Belhydromet | Belarus all-time record 40.4°C | Belhydromet | Jun 28 | Verified Fact | High |\n| 13 | SNCF | Paris region train withdrawals / track temperature | SNCF via France24 | Jun 23 | Official Statement | High |\n| 14 | EDF | Golfech nuclear shutdown / output reduction | EDF via MIT Technology Review | Jun 24 | Official Statement | Very High |\n| 15 | Deutsche Bahn | Nonessential travel advisory / GSM-R failure | Deutsche Bahn via ABC News / Xinhua | Jun 24, 27 | Official Statement | High |\n| 16 | SNCB/Infrabel | 100 trains/day cut / high-speed restrictions | SNCB/Infrabel via Xinhua | Jun 24 | Official Statement | High |\n| 17 | CFL | Track buckling Berchem-Howald | CFL via RTL Today | Jun 27 | Official Statement | High |\n| 18 | French authorities | 74 drowning deaths since June 18 | French authorities via Euronews | Jun 29 | Official Statement | Moderate |\n| 19 | Polish authorities | 17 drownings in single day | Polish authorities via AFP | Jun 29 | Official Statement | Moderate |\n| 20 | German authorities | 7 heat-related deaths | German authorities via Euronews | Jun 29 | Official Statement | Moderate |\n| 21 | Montel News | Belgian €1/kWh electricity price | Montel News via Euronews | Jun 25 | Verified Fact | High |\n| 22 | AleaSoft | Belgian weekly average €148.34/MWh; daily peak €257.55/MWh | AleaSoft | Jun 30 | Verified Fact | High |\n| 23 | EU JRC MARS Bulletin | Maize / potato yield projections | EU Joint Research Centre | Jun 30 | Expert Opinion / Verified Fact | High |\n| 24 | Wikifarmer | Agricultural impact compilation | Wikifarmer | Jun 30 | Verified Fact | Moderate |\n| 25 | Allianz Trade | Economic impact projections ($240B France by 2030) | Allianz Trade via Euronews | Jun 19 | Expert Opinion | Moderate |\n| 26 | ECB / Univ of Mannheim | EU output loss 0.3% in 2025, 0.8% by 2029 | European Economic Review | 2026 | Independent Verification | High |\n| 27 | Climate Analytics | Household income reduction ~3% across Europe | Climate Analytics via Euronews | Jun 25 | Independent Verification | High |\n| 28 | MIT Technology Review | AC penetration data / adaptation analysis | MIT Technology Review | Jun 24-25 | Verified Fact / Analysis | Very High |\n| 29 | IEA | AC penetration statistics | International Energy Agency | 2025 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 30 | Copernicus ECMWF | ERA5 temperature anomaly data | Copernicus Climate Change Service | Jun 2026 | Verified Fact | Very High |\n| 31 | Euronews | Compilation reporting on multiple aspects | Euronews | Jun 19-29 | News Reporting | High |\n| 32 | Currys | UK fan sales +3,000% | Currys via EU Perspectives | Jun 26 | Verified Fact | Moderate |\n| 33 | Madrid city government | Climate shelters network expansion | Madrid city government via EU Perspectives | Jun 26 | Official Statement | Moderate |\n| 34 | Climameter | Attributable temperature anomaly analysis | Climameter consortium | Jun 24 | Independent Verification | High |\n\n---\n\n*This analysis was prepared by the Editorial Intelligence Unit of THE BREAKDOWN. Fact-checking and source verification were conducted against original statements, verified data, and published reports. Confidence scores reflect source reliability, methodological transparency, and degree of corroboration. All data is current as of July 1, 2026.*\n\n*For corrections, updates, or additional evidence, contact research@thebreakdown.com.*"
