        "body": "### Indicator Dashboard\n\n| Indicator | Current Status | Trend | Source |\n|-----------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| CPI Score (0-100) | 39/100 | → Stagnant (decade) | TI 2025 |\n| RTI pending appeals | 4,13,972 | ↑ Growing 26% YoY | SNS 2025 |\n| CIC commissioners | 2 of 11 | ↓ Defunct trajectory | SNS 2025 |\n| Defunct SICs (2024-25) | 6 | ↑ Worse | SNS 2025 |\n| Penalty cases with action | 1.2% | → Minimal | CIC 2024-25 |\n| Lokpal inquiry wing | Non-functional | → 12 years stalled | Parl. Committee |\n| Portal-reliable states | 10 of 28 | → Partial | RTI Wiki 2026 |\n| Journalists killed (2025) | 4-8 | ↓ Worse | IFJ/CPJ |\n| Freedom House score | 62/100 (Partly Free) | → Declining since 2014 | FH 2026 |\n| Govt transparency (FH) | 3/4 (moderate) | → Weakened | FH 2026 |\n| Electoral Bonds | Struck down Feb 2024 | ↑ Improved | SC 2024 |\n\n### Global Comparisons: CPI 2025 — Selected Countries\n\n| Country | CPI Score | Global Rank | Key Context |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| Denmark | 89 | 1 | 8th consecutive year at top |\n| Singapore | 84 | 3 | Best in Asia |\n| New Zealand | 81 | 4 (tie) | Declining from 91 in 2012 |\n| United Kingdom | 70 | 20 | Down from 80 in 2018 |\n| United States | 64 | 29 | Down from 76 in 2015 |\n| South Korea | 64 | 29 (tie) | Improving: +8 since 2012 |\n| Estonia | 76 | 12 | Top post-Soviet improver |\n| China | 43 | 73 | Questionable data sources |\n| South Africa | 43 | 73 (tie) | Declining from 45 in 2014 |\n| India | 39 | 91 | Stagnant for a decade |\n| Brazil | 35 | 104 | Declined from 43 in 2014 |\n| Pakistan | 28 | 136 | Persistent low score |\n| Bangladesh | 24 | 150 | Declining from 29 in 2015 |\n| Somalia | 9 | 182 (bottom) | Conflict-affected |\n| Afghanistan | 16 | 169 | Collapsed after 2021 |\n\n**Verified Fact.** Source: Transparency International, CPI 2025 full ranking table. Confidence: 100."
