        "title": "Why This Matters",
        "body": "MGNREGA was the world's largest public works programme. In 2024-25, it covered **15.99 crore registered households** — more people than the population of Brazil and Russia combined. It generated **290.60 crore person-days of employment** and spent approximately ₹86,000 crore. To put that in perspective: ₹86,000 crore is roughly 0.3% of India's GDP, or about half of what the central government spends on fertilizer subsidies in a year. For millions of landless labourers, small farmers, and women in rural India, this programme is the primary safety net between subsistence and destitution.\n\n**Verified Fact.** Source: PIB, Ministry of Rural Development, August 2025; MGNREGA MIS dashboard. Confidence: 100.\n\nAny change to this programme affects more people than most laws passed by Parliament. The replacement — pushed through in the winter session of 2025 amid opposition protests — alters the legal character of the employment guarantee, the financial burden on states, and the method by which funds reach workers.\n\n**Official Statement.** Source: Lok Sabha debates, December 2025; Presidential assent December 21, 2025. Confidence: 100."
