    "summary": "On June 26, 2026, India's Department of Atomic Energy commissioned the world's first hydrogen production facility that uses nuclear reactor heat — not electricity — to split water. The Copper-Chlorine thermochemical plant at Kalpakkam operates 24/7, weather-independent, producing zero greenhouse gas emissions by drawing process heat from the Fast Breeder Test Reactor.",
