        "type": "explained",
        "title": "Safety Concerns",
        "body": "Anthropic built safety classifiers into Fable 5 that block queries related to cyberattacks, biological weapons, and chemical weapons. On June 12, the company deemed these insufficient and suspended access to both models. On June 22, Fable 5 was removed from standard subscription plans and shifted to a usage-credit model, further narrowing public availability. The pattern — release, restrict, retreat — tracks an organisation struggling to reconcile commercial pressure with safety obligations. Anthropic's dual-model strategy was widely viewed as a reasonable compromise. Its rapid suspension demonstrates that no current framework offers a reliable path for deploying AI this capable at scale."
