        "type": "explained",
        "title": "Industry Response",
        "body": "Cybersecurity firms have hailed Mythos as a potential breakthrough for vulnerability research while privately expressing concern about its applicability in offensive contexts. Competing AI laboratories are watching closely: if Anthropic cannot manage Mythos's deployment, no company with a less rigorous safety culture can claim to manage comparable systems. The episode has intensified the debate about whether the AI industry is prepared to govern frontier models without regulatory compulsion. Anthropic's approach — restricted high-capability for trusted partners, safety-filtered for the public — is regarded as the current state of the art in responsible deployment. The speed of its failure suggests the state of the art is not yet adequate."
