        "body": "Mythos has become a reference case for regulators worldwide. The UK AISI's April 13 evaluation was among the first independent assessments of a model's capacity for autonomous harm. The European Union's AI Act, still in implementation, may require revision to account for models that can discover zero-day vulnerabilities faster than human researchers. The US executive order on AI safety did not anticipate self-censorship by the model's creator as a primary safeguard. Anthropic's suspension of access implies that existing regulatory frameworks lack the specificity to govern frontier AI, and that companies must self-regulate in the absence of guidance. Mythos is the first AI whose builders concluded it was too capable to release without a safety kill-switch. The questions it raises will define AI governance for the next decade."
